                  <persName id="t18150405-153-person1296">
                  MARY 
                  WINDHAM
               <interp inst="t18150405-153-person1296" type="surname" value="WINDHAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18150405-153-person1296" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18150405-153-person1296" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am shopwoman to Mr. Dawson. The prisoner came into the shop with a young woman with her; she asked to look at some lace; I shewed her some; she said they were not broad enough; she took up one bit of lace, and asked the price of it; I told her eight shillings and sixpence; she concealed it in her hand, and asked the price of another. I then informed Mr. Dawson that the prisoner had concealed a piece of lace in her hand.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I had seven shillings in my pocket to pay for it, and halfpence besides.</p>
               <p>The prisoner called five witnesses, who gave her a good character.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18150405-153-verdict851" type="verdictDescription">
